    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 1994 Mazda RX-7 FD remains a pinnacle of Japanese engineering, powered by the 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary engine. The powerplant exhibits strong compression across all rotors, benefiting from a recent vacuum line simplification and an upgraded aluminum radiator to manage thermal loads effectively. Power is routed through a precise five-speed manual transmission to a Torsen limited-slip differential, while the lightweight chassis retains its superb 50/50 weight distribution and double-wishbone suspension geometry. This example features a well-preserved interior and a mechanically sound drivetrain, free of common boost leaks or synchro grind. A purist\u2019s machine optimized for cornering transients and high-revving performance.",
      "price": 32500.0,
